{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/hot-reload-env-files","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"vue-cli-plugin-envhot\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#vue-cli-plugin-envhot\" aria-label=\"vue cli plugin envhot permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>vue-cli-plugin-envhot</h1>\n<p>Seamlessly add .env file hot reloading support for your vue-cli based projects. Never worry about rebooting webpack-dev-server again.</p>\n<h2 id=\"features--tips\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#features--tips\" aria-label=\"features  tips permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Features &#x26; Tips</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Reference <a href=\"https://cli.vuejs.org/guide/mode-and-env.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Here</a> for usage of .env file.</li>\n<li>Modify .env files in runtime and have it dynamically injected into your application</li>\n<li>Support modification, addtion, deletion of field in .env files</li>\n<li>Only works in development mode. In production mode you won't need hot reload anyway.</li>\n<li>Priority of file is <code class=\"language-text\">[&quot;.env.development.local&quot;, &quot;.env.development&quot;, &quot;.env.local&quot;, &quot;.env&quot;]</code>, i.e., value with same key defined in '.env.local' will overwrite value defined in '.env'</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"installation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#installation\" aria-label=\"installation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Installation</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">yarn</span> <span class=\"token function\">add</span> vue-cli-plugin-envhot</code></pre></div>\n<p>OR</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> -S vue-cli-plugin-envhot</code></pre></div>","excerpt":"vue-cli-plugin-envhot Seamlessly add .env file hot reloading support for your vue-cli based projects. Never worry about rebooting webpackâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Hot reload .env files","date":"08.09.2020","category":"Packages"},"timeToRead":1}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/hot-reload-env-files","prev":{"fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/owenwang/Documents/javascript/serializedowen.github.io/blog/2018-12-29/index.md","fields":{"slug":"/ice-skiing"},"sourceType":"posts","frontmatter":{"title":"Ic